%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to jump, to leap","examples":[{"text":"الطِّفْلُ قَفَزَ فَرْحًا عِنْدَ رُؤْيَةِ الْهِدَايَا.","english":"The child jumped with joy upon seeing the gifts."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to die"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of قَفَزَ (qafaza, “to jump”) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"jumping"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Aramaic קְפַט (qp̄aṭ), Classical Syriac ܩܦ݂ܲܛ (qfaṭ) and Hebrew קָפַץ (kafáts, “to jump”)."},"ipa":["/qa.fa.za/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n36037","headword_ar":"قَفَزَ","root":"qfz","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qafozN","text_ar":"قَفْزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qafazaAnN","text_ar":"قَفَزَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qufuwzN","text_ar":"قُفُوزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qifaAzN","text_ar":"قِفَازٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, and so in a copy of the K,) the last with kesr, (Msb,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qufaAzN","text_ar":"قُفَازٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K accord. to the TA,) with damm, (TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qafaAzN","text_ar":"قَفَازٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in the CK,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He leaped, jumped, sprang,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bounded:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he"},{"kind":"text","text":"(an antelope)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"did so and alighted with his legs together."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nfz","text_ar":"نفز"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qafaza AlHaAy^iTa","text_ar":"قَفَزَ الحَايِطَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He leaped the wall"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zyf","text_ar":"زيف"},{"kind":"text","text":".)       -A2-  See also 5.       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qafiza","text_ar":"قَفِزَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qafaza","text_ar":"قَفَزَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a horse)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had fore legs white as high as his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mirofaqaAni","text_ar":"مِرْفَقَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[properly signifying the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"elbows;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but here, probably meaning, as it seems to do in some other instances, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knees"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"but not the kind legs."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IKtt, TA. [And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quf~iza","text_ar":"قُفِّزَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"app. has a similar meaning: see its inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tqfyz","text_ar":"تقفيز"},{"kind":"text","text":"below; and its part. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muqaf~azN","text_ar":"مُقَفَّزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqofazu","text_ar":"اَقْفَزُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) But see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqofazu","text_ar":"اَقْفَزُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quf~aAzN","text_ar":"قُفَّازٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"kind":"page_break","n":2551}],"source_refs":["S","A","Msb","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}